         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">12/7/86 ¶  ¶  ¶ In first instance, dear Mr Carruthers, let me offer my best felicita- ¶ Word, at end of line, has not been completed. ¶  ¶ to your being raised to the Presidentship of the now venerabl...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.07.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Carruthers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Natural History Museum, London, Museum Archives, DF404/5, folder 71,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Mueller, Sir FJH von.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12/7/86<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In first instance, dear Mr Carruthers, let me offer my best felicita-<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Word, at end of line, has not been completed.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to your being raised to the Presidentship of the now venerable Linnean Society, which as a worthy successor of Smith, Brown, Bentham, Lubbock, and so many other illustrious men you will hold with so much dignity!<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Edward Smith, Robert Brown (1773-1858), George Bentham, John Lubbock.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>So it will fall to your share, to preside at the Society’s centenary Jubilee!<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>24 May 1888.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>You being still young, I trust you will hold this highly distinguished position through very many years, like some of your predecessors.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>William Carruthers was elected President of the Linnean Society of London on 24 May 1886, and served for four years (Gage &amp; Stearn<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(1988), p. 219).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It was me, who moved for a joint antarctic Committee here, to give the Home Committee some help; and it was also on my proposition, that our Senior Naval Explorer, Capt Pascoe, was made chairman here.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have done all preliminaries in sorting and arranging Mr Forbes plants, and have just elaborated his<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Sterculiae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with other Papuan species from various sources.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Henry Forbes;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>B86.08.03<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>included several species represented in Forbes's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>collection, including the new species<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Sterculia oncinocarpa</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>attributed to M and Forbes, p. 49.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You and Mr Ridley will be doubtless able to utilize the msc, sent two weeks ago, on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Vaccinieae; and I anticipate, that Mr Britten will be glad, to publish it with such notes, as you may append.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Britten was the editor of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Journal of botany</seg>, in which M’s descriptions appeared (B86.10.01). The following note is included:<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>.In a letter accompanying the above descriptions, Baron von Mueller has asked me to compare them with the larger series of Mr Forbes’s specimens received at the British Museum, and to add any additional characters which these might supply. I find scarcely anything to supplement his description, but with regard to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Agapetes Forbesii</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>it may be noted that the peduncles are contracted. Mr. Forbes’s No. 768 (from Mount Wori-Wori, 5000 ft.) also belongs to this species. — W. Fawcett.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>remembrance your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I hope to make soon good progress with Mr Forbes's plants, particularly as his specimens become completed in many instances by what I had from others.</p>
         </div>
